Description:
The Centre for Labour Research (CLR) is a non-profit organization working on labour rights issues and producing cutting-edge research on employment rights in a comparative perspective, both at the national and international level.
Would you like to join a team of employment rights experts for exciting comparative labour law work? Do you want to help bring change in the lives of common people by providing easy-to-understand information to make them aware about their labour rights? Are you interested in being part of the national level policy reforms by drafting legislative policy briefs on the much-needed reforms for the ever-growing labour force in the country? Pakistan alone has a labour force of more than 70 million, thus, the scope of work is enormous!
If you are what we are looking for, you will get a chance to do innovative work in a unique field of research!
Research Associate - Qualifications and Experience
Education
LLB/LLM from University of London.
Work Experience
At least three year experience in report writing
Job Discription
· Gather, compile information and support research related to workplace rights in Pakistan and other countries, including statistical analysis, a review of existing research in topics such as employment legislation and all topics related to Decent Work Agenda*;
· Assist in the preparation of various documentation and reports on workplace rights, both at the country level and in comparative context;
· Engage in knowledge and information management activities such as the development of tools, products, methodologies and programmes on employment legislation, systematizing existing information by date, topic and country;
· Assist in the organization of conferences, workshops, seminars, forums or other collaborative events in the context of the workplace rights and awareness-raising among the masses;
· Assist in developing compliance tools enabling employers to comply with labour legislation;
· Submit newspaper data on workplace rights violations through the Whistlers platform;
· Confirm the reliability of data by contacting those submitting reports through the Whistlers;
· Assist in research reports on achievement of targets under SDGs, especially those relating to workplace rights, gender equality and tourism; and
· Perform other relevant tasks as assigned by the supervisor
Skills
Good research writing skills - Ability to write technical reports, information notes and summaries among others;
Content management and development - Ability to design communication supports (such as presentations, brochures), and to produce website and social media content;
Proficiency in IT (WORD, POWER POINT, EXCEL etc.) and internet usage.
Competencies
Capacity to work independently, plan activities and resolve challenges;
Ability to work in a team, share and listen to ideas;
Good communication skills, both written and verbal;
Ability to work in a multicultural and gender-sensitive environment.
Job Type: Full-time
Salary: From Rs35,000.00 per month
Ability to commute/relocate:

Rawalpindi: Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Required)

Education:

Master's (Required)
